1
00:00:07,374 --> 00:00:09,943
When the door opened, it all came together.

2
00:00:09,943 --> 00:00:12,746
And so rain or shine, we made it through.

3
00:00:12,746 --> 00:00:16,850
But again, the phrases that I heard the most
were "let's go" and "we got this."

4
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:18,919
OLIVE YOUNG is planting a new flag,

5
00:00:18,919 --> 00:00:21,121
something truly unprecedented
in the US beauty market,

6
00:00:21,121 --> 00:00:23,123
and I get to be part of that moment!

7
00:01:00,928 --> 00:01:02,896
In terms of size alone,

8
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:05,666
the US accounts for roughly 20%
of the global beauty market,

9
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:07,267
making it the largest beauty market in the world.

10
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,237
Brands and categories that trend in the US

11
00:01:10,237 --> 00:01:13,974
often have a significant influence
on the global market as a whole.

12
00:01:13,974 --> 00:01:16,043
Since 2018,

13
00:01:16,043 --> 00:01:17,911
through our cross-border e-commerce business
(OLIVE YOUNG Global Mall),

14
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:21,215
the US has consistently generated
the highest sales.

15
00:01:21,215 --> 00:01:24,184
Taking all of these factors into consideration,

16
00:01:24,184 --> 00:01:29,089
we concluded that the US
is an ideal strategic market for OLIVE YOUNG.

17
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:32,326
I think just what really works in the market

18
00:01:32,326 --> 00:01:38,031
is that in the US, customers and just the public
really want to focus on the "why."

19
00:01:38,031 --> 00:01:40,634
And that there's
a little bit of a story behind it.

20
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:43,237
And I think what OLIVE YOUNG
is really great at is that

21
00:01:43,237 --> 00:01:47,307
just by seeing like the range
of the brands and the products that we carry,

22
00:01:47,307 --> 00:01:50,844
we don't just sell the popular products
that are viral on social media.

23
00:01:50,844 --> 00:01:53,313
We stand with individual growing brands.

24
00:01:53,313 --> 00:01:55,983
We grow with them to continue their journey.

25
00:01:55,983 --> 00:02:00,420
The first thing I had to do was really plan
and align and come up with a strategy

26
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:04,591
as it was going to be the first store
opening in the United States of America.

27
00:02:04,591 --> 00:02:08,028
So, ensuring that a plan was in place,

28
00:02:08,028 --> 00:02:12,332
hiring the right staff
to support the OLIVE YOUNG culture,

29
00:02:12,332 --> 00:02:16,303
and really listening and fine-tuning
to all of our Korean team members

30
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:20,541
to really understand and gauge
what was expected from them

31
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:25,212
to ensure that we ran a well-oiled machine
leading up to the grand opening in Pasadena.

32
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:31,582
One thing we kept hearing
from our overseas partners

33
00:02:31,583 --> 00:02:34,620
while preparing for this project was,

34
00:02:34,621 --> 00:02:37,658
"Retail can't cross borders."

35
00:02:37,658 --> 00:02:42,429
Convincing major brands
who we are, what kind of retailer we are,

36
00:02:42,429 --> 00:02:47,100
and what we could achieve together
through collaboration

37
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,504
was probably the most challenging part.

38
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:54,007
Sometimes we leveraged connections
through our merchandising teams in Korea.

39
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:56,310
Other times, we sent cold emails,

40
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:58,345
reached out through LinkedIn,

41
00:02:58,345 --> 00:02:59,913
and even sent flower baskets.

42
00:02:59,913 --> 00:03:02,883
We tried every possible way to break through.

43
00:03:02,883 --> 00:03:04,651
We needed to build relationships somehow

44
00:03:04,651 --> 00:03:06,987
and let people know
that we had entered this market.

45
00:03:06,987 --> 00:03:10,791
We also had to instill confidence
that we were going to succeed here,

46
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:13,160
so we reached out in every way we could.

47
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:18,031
I think the challenge
of opening the first US store

48
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,766
was not knowing the unknown.

49
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:23,212
For example, receiving shipments

50
00:03:23,213 --> 00:03:27,574
and receiving collateral
and receiving product for our store.

51
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:30,994
Maybe some form of streamlining
or more planning and aligning

52
00:03:30,995 --> 00:03:35,549
to ensure that
what was being placed out on the sales floor

53
00:03:35,549 --> 00:03:38,252
differed from what we needed to put
in the back stock.

54
00:03:38,252 --> 00:03:40,320
Our team worked tirelessly.

55
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,859
Taking everything that we learned from Korea,

56
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:47,326
taking the things that we learned
from our HQ partners,

57
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:53,267
whether it was human resources,
marketing, IT, POS,

58
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:55,435
all of them played a huge role

59
00:03:55,435 --> 00:03:59,873
to ensure that we collaborated
and cured any nuance that was happening

60
00:03:59,873 --> 00:04:01,479
leading to the grand opening.

61
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:05,579
So, again, huge kudos
to playing a huge part in teamwork,

62
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:07,080
because without the teamwork,

63
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,317
we would not be where we're at
in finalizing the grand opening.

64
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,389
What an exciting day!

65
00:04:15,389 --> 00:04:18,525
I believe today
is more than just the store opening.

66
00:04:18,525 --> 00:04:22,606
It's a special moment
where Korean beauty and wellness culture

67
00:04:22,607 --> 00:04:26,834
begin to form a meaningful connection
with our vibrant Pasadena community

68
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,536
that we all love so much.

69
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:30,537
3

70
00:04:30,537 --> 00:04:31,438
2

71
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:32,406
1

72
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:36,410
Welcome to OLIVE YOUNG!

73
00:04:36,410 --> 00:04:38,890
When the door opened, it all came together

74
00:04:38,891 --> 00:04:43,717
and seeing my team just working day and night
and running around to just make this happen,

75
00:04:43,717 --> 00:04:47,487
putting some of their personal obligations aside,
was very touching for me.

76
00:04:47,487 --> 00:04:50,157
Everyone's collaboration,
everyone's communication,

77
00:04:50,157 --> 00:04:53,827
everyone's focus to win was there.

78
00:04:53,827 --> 00:04:57,431
And so, rain or shine, we made it through.

79
00:04:57,431 --> 00:05:01,835
But again, the phrases that I heard the most
were "let's go" and "we got this."

80
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:04,071
I remember feeling really emotional
at that moment.

81
00:05:04,071 --> 00:05:08,542
It was like,
"Wow, it's really happening."

82
00:05:08,542 --> 00:05:10,589
OLIVE YOUNG is planting a new flag,

83
00:05:10,590 --> 00:05:12,912
something truly unprecedented
in the US beauty market,

84
00:05:12,913 --> 00:05:15,015
and I get to be part of that moment!

85
00:05:21,788 --> 00:05:24,391
When people first heard that OLIVE YOUNG
was entering the US market,

86
00:05:24,391 --> 00:05:28,795
they would ask,
"So, are you like Sephora? CVS? Or Ulta?"

87
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:30,731
We got that question a lot.

88
00:05:30,731 --> 00:05:33,400
But what we took pride in was

89
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:37,685
being a retailer unlike anything
the US market had seen before.

90
00:05:37,686 --> 00:05:39,406
One that constantly brings
something new and fresh to the market.

91
00:05:39,406 --> 00:05:41,392
We wanted to be known as a destination

92
00:05:41,393 --> 00:05:44,186
that delivers fresh discoveries
and experiences to customers.

93
00:05:44,187 --> 00:05:46,633
A place so fun and exciting

94
00:05:46,634 --> 00:05:50,383
that once you step inside,
you never want to leave.

95
00:05:50,384 --> 00:05:54,788
The number of our customers
that were at the beauty lab during grand opening,

96
00:05:54,788 --> 00:05:57,337
the amount of customers
that wanted that skin scan,

97
00:05:57,338 --> 00:05:59,338
that scalp scan, really stood out to me

98
00:06:00,460 --> 00:06:04,298
because there isn't anything
comparable to that in the US

99
00:06:04,298 --> 00:06:06,567
from other competitors, right?

100
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:09,603
And so, something that will evolve

101
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:14,474
and separate us from the other retailers
is that technology.

102
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:17,477
I think just what's so interesting for me

103
00:06:17,477 --> 00:06:23,252
was that as I was walking around the store,
I heard a lot of questions asking the sales staff.

104
00:06:23,253 --> 00:06:24,184
It wasn't essentially,

105
00:06:24,184 --> 00:06:26,587
"Hey, where can I find this serum?"

106
00:06:26,587 --> 00:06:28,322
"Where can I find this mask pack?"

107
00:06:28,322 --> 00:06:33,224
But they're actually addressing their concerns
in more of a counseling form, asking,

108
00:06:33,225 --> 00:06:36,129
"Hey, I have dry skin.
What would you recommend?"

109
00:06:36,129 --> 00:06:38,295
"I want to improve my dark spots."

110
00:06:38,296 --> 00:06:40,933
"Which product would you recommend from which shelf? "

111
00:06:40,934 --> 00:06:45,339
And I think this really kind of shows
that the brand has succeeded

112
00:06:45,339 --> 00:06:48,342
in where they aim to be in curating this experience.

113
00:06:48,342 --> 00:06:50,978
We're not just here to sell product.

114
00:06:50,978 --> 00:06:55,171
We're here to build a lifestyle for our customers,

115
00:06:55,172 --> 00:06:58,685
our people in the LA market,
or everywhere nationwide.

116
00:06:58,685 --> 00:07:01,121
When you're building that connection
with your customer,

117
00:07:01,121 --> 00:07:04,625
whether it's through human connection
or technology,

118
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:08,211
you're really going to see
a huge difference of building trust,

119
00:07:08,212 --> 00:07:10,096
your connection with your customers,

120
00:07:10,097 --> 00:07:14,234
because we are a lifestyle
that nobody else can touch.

121
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:21,909
Going forward, to become
a trendsetting beauty retailer

122
00:07:21,909 --> 00:07:24,378
and a beauty leader in the market,

123
00:07:24,378 --> 00:07:26,280
we will continue to source
not only K-beauty brands,

124
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:29,917
but also a diverse range of global brands.

125
00:07:29,917 --> 00:07:33,954
By curating them in our own unique way,

126
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:35,956
we aim to create experiences unlike anything
the market has seen before.

127
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:39,159
Unique touchpoints that customers can experience
only at OLIVE YOUNG.

128
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:44,831
I'm sure that we'll continue to build
the culture and the DNA of OLIVE YOUNG.

129
00:07:44,831 --> 00:07:47,901
We learned so much about OLIVE YOUNG in Korea,

130
00:07:47,901 --> 00:07:54,074
and I feel it's my responsibility to continue
that DNA and the culture here in the US,

131
00:07:54,074 --> 00:07:57,377
and continue the DNA
through our third, our fourth,

132
00:07:57,377 --> 00:08:00,347
and our hundredth store
that we have in the future.

133
00:08:00,347 --> 00:08:06,353
What I'm looking for is to really be
that No.1 beauty retailer by the year 2030,

134
00:08:06,353 --> 00:08:10,691
and how we're going to do that
is to really maintain the brand authenticity,

135
00:08:10,691 --> 00:08:13,427
not in terms of the product,
but just in the brand value.

136
00:08:13,427 --> 00:08:17,030
So it's always just innovate,
be excited, come up with new ideas,

137
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:22,569
and not be afraid to bring those up
and really just make it happen and deliver.

